column5: Can someone share the results from this event? Thanks in advance.

Just trying to get yesterdays final weights. First day was much better then the tournament two weekends ago. More consistency nearly all the way to the bottom of the teams. Nearly 24#'s for 4 fish first day was tops.

Quote from another forum. I was not in the tournament. 1-10th ranged from 42+lbs to 37+lbs. Big fish each day was 10.5 and 10.6. A lot of boats stuck out the rough water and fished the bay and generally i would say they were rewarded for it, with the exception of one boat which is now at the bottom of the lake. We managed to place 7th.
I spoke with Mike at the Papertown Inn to get the results for the tournament. Click on Day 2 Results to get a pdf of the Day 2 and combined results.http://www.papertowninn.ca/fishing.htm
